In [20]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import PolynomialFeatures 
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, r2_score
# simple linear regression degree 1
lr = LinearRegression()
lr.fit(x_train, y_train)
y_pred = lr.predict(x_test)
print('Simple linear regression score: ', lr.score(x_train, y_train))
sns.residplot(x_test['cement'], y_pred, color='black', lowess=True)
sns.residplot(x_train['cement'], y_train, color='green', lowess=True)
# The mean squared error:linear regression
print('Mean squared error LR: ', mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred))
# Explained variance score: 1 is perfect prediction
print('Test Variance score LR: %.2f'% r2_score(y_test, y_pred))

# polynomial regression
poly = PolynomialFeatures( degree = 3, include_bias = False) 
xpoly_train = poly.fit_transform(x_train)
lr_poly = lr.fit(xpoly_train, y_train)
xpoly_test = poly.fit_transform(x_test)
ypred_poly = lr.predict(xpoly_test)
print('Polynomial regression:', lr_poly.score(xpoly_train, y_train))
# The mean squared error:polynomial regression
print('Mean squared error PR: ', mean_squared_error(y_test, ypred_poly))
# Explained variance score: 1 is perfect prediction
print('Test Variance score PR: %.2f'% r2_score(y_test, ypred_poly))

K-fold cross validation¶

In [96]:
# K-fold validation has to be performed on the training data (modified with a polynomial fit)
from sklearn import model_selection
from sklearn.svm import SVR
from sklearn.ensemble import BaggingRegressor
from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingRegressor
kfold = model_selection.KFold(n_splits=20)

# Model: Linear Regressor
result_lr = model_selection.cross_val_score(lr, xpoly_train, y_train, scoring='r2', cv=kfold)
result_lr_ev = model_selection.cross_val_score(lr, xpoly_train, y_train, scoring='explained_variance', cv=kfold)
print("Mean r2 Score (Linear Regressor): %.3f (%.3f)" % (result_lr.mean(), result_lr.std()))
print("Mean estimated variance score (Linear Regressor): %.3f (%.3f)" % (result_lr_ev.mean(), result_lr_ev.std()))

# Model: Decision Tree Regressor
result_dt = model_selection.cross_val_score(dtr, xpoly_train, y_train, scoring='r2',cv=kfold)
result_dt_ev = model_selection.cross_val_score(dtr, xpoly_train, y_train, scoring='explained_variance',cv=kfold)
print("Mean r2 Score (Decision Tree Regressor): %.3f (%.3f)" % (result_dt.mean(), result_dt.std()))
print("Mean estimated variance score (Decision Tree Regressor): %.3f (%.3f)" % (result_dt_ev.mean(), result_dt_ev.std()))

# Model: Bagging Regressor
br = BaggingRegressor(base_estimator=dtr, n_estimators=50, random_state=1).fit(xpoly_train, y_train)
result_br_ev = model_selection.cross_val_score(br, xpoly_train, y_train, scoring='explained_variance', cv=kfold)
result_br = model_selection.cross_val_score(br, xpoly_train, y_train, scoring='r2', cv=kfold)
print("Mean r2 Score (Bagging Regressor): %.3f (%.3f)" % (result_br.mean(), result_br.std()))
print("Mean estimated variance score (Bagging Regressor): %.3f (%.3f)" % (result_br_ev.mean(), result_br_ev.std()))

# Model: Gradient Boosting Regressor
gbr = GradientBoostingRegressor(n_estimators = 20, learning_rate = 0.1, max_depth=5 , random_state=22).fit(xpoly_train, y_train)
result_gbr_ev = model_selection.cross_val_score(gbr, xpoly_train, y_train, scoring='explained_variance', cv=kfold)
result_gbr = model_selection.cross_val_score(gbr, xpoly_train, y_train, scoring='r2', cv=kfold)
print("Mean r2 Score (Gradient Boosting Regressor): %.3f (%.3f)" % (result_gbr.mean(), result_gbr.std()))
print("Mean estimated variance score (Gradient Boosting Regressor): %.3f (%.3f)" % (result_gbr_ev.mean(), result_gbr_ev.std()))

Mean r2 Score (Linear Regressor): 0.847 (0.066)
Mean estimated variance score (Linear Regressor): 0.852 (0.062)
Mean r2 Score (Decision Tree Regressor): 0.750 (0.117)
Mean estimated variance score (Decision Tree Regressor): 0.754 (0.118)
Mean r2 Score (Bagging Regressor): 0.883 (0.036)
Mean estimated variance score (Bagging Regressor): 0.885 (0.035)
Mean r2 Score (Gradient Boosting Regressor): 0.851 (0.037)
Mean estimated variance score (Gradient Boosting Regressor): 0.855 (0.035)
